    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Small rugs of approximately 3 by 5 feet, often with a design that incorporates some depiction of a mihrab; originally intended for Islamic prayer, although some motifs and inscriptions indicate not all were made for this purpose.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
